title: For Sale:  AR-15 Custom Build
postcontent:
This AR-15 was built by a local gunsmith with the goal of making a highly accurate and extremely reliable assault rifle.
The AR is built on an Anderson Lower with a precision lower parts kit, custom trigger and high-quality AM bolt carrier group.  The upper is a rigid MilSpec MUR-1S with an integrated MilStd-1913 scope mounting rail.  This upper has thicker walls than traditional AR-15s which extends the life of the bolt carrier group and barrel interface.
The handguard is a Troy hardened aircraft aluminum free-float rail which can easily be customized to the operator's preferences.  
It has front and rear MBUS sights and a Magpul grip and collapsible stock.  
It comes with four 30 round magazines and polymer rail sections to mount your accessories to the handguard.
It has about 500 rounds through it and is in excellent condition.  
Why buy a mass produced, plastic AR-15 when you can have this locally built, tough as nails custom assault rifle for hundreds less than it's worth!

title: For Sale/Trade:  Russian SKS-45
postcontent:
I have for sale/trade a nice Russian SKS, this particular SKS is somewhat rare and is what is known as a "Letter Gun" or "Letter Series" SKS, Google it to find out if you don't know, but basically it was the last of the SKS's produced by Russia, they are believed to have been made around 1955-1957, this particular one is the "I" model, denoted by the Cyrillic "N" after the last digit of the S/N, there also were "D" and "K" models.

These are also known as "Side Star" SKS's due to the Tula star being on the side.

When I bought it it had a craptastic Tapco stock on it, and a tall as heck scope mount receiver cover. I took all that off(NO LONGER HAVE THE STUFF) and fit it into a Norinco Stock, with the standard Receiver Cover, it's why it has the Spike Bayonet, it is a Russian SKS! I just refinished the Stock and Hand guard as well. Has a cleaning kit in the trapdoor in the buttstock, only thing it's missing is the Cleaning Rod, would make a nice addition to a collection or a nice shooter, it does function FLAWLESSLY, and doesn't slam fire! No ammo is included at this price, and look up the Russian SKS's before you start commenting on my price, they are going for more than $550 everywhere else, these are the best quality SKS that was produced, the milling was fantastic, and it's all milled parts, NO STAMPED!

Only trade I'm looking for is a Taurus PT92 or PT917, would like the Stainless model, and will include ammo if I receive ammo, will match round for round, I have 280 rounds of which 100 is ready to go on 10 round stripper clips.

title: For Sale:  FEG FP9 – NIB; 9mm Pistol; Browning High Power Clone
postcontent:
Pistol is BRAND NEW, in its original box, with an extra 13-round magazine, manual, and cleaning rod.  Never fired. Mint condition. All original parts included.  Factory walnut grips, fixed sights, and the rare vented rib. Made in Hungary by FEG. Imported by CIA, St. Albans, VT. 

After the original Browning patents for the Browning Hi-Power (BHP) expired, the Hungarian conglomerate of FÉG developed one of the most faithful versions of the Browning design ever made in quantity outside the FN factories in Belgium and Portugal. The BHP and the FP9 are so similar that many parts are interchangeable between them, including the magazines.

This pistol feels great in the hand – exactly like my 1981 BHP.  Note: the non-vented rib version of this pistol was exported as PJK-9HP/P9M models.

For FTF sale in VA, buyer must be 21+ years of age and have (1) a VA driver’s license, and (2) one of the following: a concealed carry permit, LEO ID, or a copy of VA gun store invoice in buyer’s name in last year. If no IDs or invoice, can transfer at a local FFL with a quick background check.  For an out-of-state sale, will arrange shipment to buyer’s FFL, at buyer’s cost.

$725 Firm. Transaction will include bill of sale. Sorry, no trades at this time. Still available if posted.
